guiSET.core

Class GuisetDefaultValues

  • java.lang.Object
    • guiSET.core.GuisetDefaultValues

  • public class GuisetDefaultValues
extends java.lang.Object
    Default values are used when constructing new objects. They can be modified to ease the styling of the gui. I.e. if the backgroundColor is set to black, gui item that are created afterwards will be defaulted with a black background etc.
